The paper proposes a method for image saliency detection, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The method also involves the use of eigendecomposition and Bayesian perspective, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of distance metrics and modeling of distributions, which are common in information retrieval. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
